  <md:content-id>m19988</md:content-id><md:title>Lesson 4 - Rights and Responsibilities in the Classroom or Playground</md:title>
  <md:abstract>At the end of this lesson, the students will: Decide between classroom rules and playground rules as a subject for their own research and persuasive position paper. Brainstorm the rights and responsibilities of classroom or playground users. Review previously prepared stakeholder positions on these issues. Fill out a provided graphic organizer using the collected information from brainstorming and stakeholder reviews. Write an individual persuasive position paper on the chosen topic.</md:abstract>
  <md:uuid>44c8b2a6-9e1f-4ab9-91f3-8089977cd3f3</md:uuid>
</metadata>

<content>
    <para id="id25362621">Step 1: Be prepared to answer the following question: Why do we have rules in school? I will write a few of your class’s answers on the white board. Next, you will help brainstorm a list of good school rules and bad school rules, which will also be recorded on the whiteboard. </para>
    <para id="id25363123">Step 2: I will write the words “Playground Rules or Classroom Rules” on the board. As a class, be prepared to vote on the one you want to research and write about. </para>
    <para id="id25363086">Step 3: Using the provided stakeholder point of view papers and blank graphic organizers, you will fill out the first two lines of the graphic organizer. When finished, go to Lesson 4 Step 4.</para>
